{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd727fd3-1864-4456-9d98-31aa76e99246","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication options (`--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example with auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --client-id <your-client-id>\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation. Want me to scaffold a project with a specific auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4aef515b-10e9-4587-86b1-bc243666dd52","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":266,"requestId":"781B:1380F:5843315:605608C:69F3FA00"},"id":"42f5468f-ca40-46ec-a9ae-8b2f4bc5339c","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:36.730Z","parentId":"3b7499a4-8050-46d2-8912-1fd9336142cd"}
